<section id="menus.edit">
  <title id="menus.edit.title">Edit</title>

  <note><para>This menu displays entries only when a project is open.</para>
  <para>Key shortcut description reminder: <link linkend="appendix.shortcut" endterm="shortcut_description"/></para>
  <example><title>Undo Last Action</title>
  		<para>In this manual:
		  <keycombo><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>z</keycap></keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>On Windows and Linux:
		  <keycombo><keycap>Control</keycap><keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo>
		</para>
		<para>On macOS:
		  <keycombo><keycap>Command</keycap><keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo>
		</para>
		</example>
  </note>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenuitem>Undo Last Action</guimenuitem></term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Restores the status before the last editing action was taken.
        This command does not work once the user has moved to a different
        segment.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>z</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Redo Last Action</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Restores the status before the last editing action was
        cancelled. This command does not work once the user has moved to a
        different segment.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>y</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Replace With Match or Selection</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Replaces the whole target segment with the currently selected
        fuzzy match (by default the first match is selected). See <link
        linkend="panes.fuzzy.matches" endterm="panes.fuzzy.matches.title"/> for
        details.</para>

        <para>Any text selected in the <link linkend="panes.fuzzy.matches"
        endterm="panes.fuzzy.matches.title"/> pane will have priority over the
        selected match and will replace the whole target segment.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>r</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Insert Match or Selection</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Inserts the currently selected fuzzy match at the cursor
        position. If part of the target segment has been selected, this
        function overwrites the selected portion. See <link
        linkend="panes.fuzzy.matches" endterm="panes.fuzzy.matches.title"/> for details.</para>

        <para>Any text selected in the <link
        linkend="panes.fuzzy.matches" endterm="panes.fuzzy.matches.title"/> pane
        will have priority over the selected match and will be inserted at the
        cursor position.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>i</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Replace with Machine Translation</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Replaces the target segment with the translation, provided by
        the selected Machine Translation service. No action is taken if no
        Machine Translation service has been activated (in <link linkend="menus.options.mt"><menuchoice>
        <guimenu>Options</guimenu>
        <guimenuitem>Machine Translate</guimenuitem></menuchoice></link>). See
        <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.mt">Machine Translation</link> for
        details.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>m</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Replace with Source</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Replaces the whole target segment with the segment source.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>r</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Insert Source</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Inserts the segment source at the cursor position.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>i</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>	
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Insert Missing Source Tags</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Inserts the remaining missing source tags at the cursor
        position.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>t</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Insert Next Missing Tag</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Inserts the next missing tag at the cursor position.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>t</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Export Selection</term>

      <listitem>
		<!-- TODO: add section for the User's preference files folder and link to it -->
        <para>Exports the current selection to a text file for processing. If
        no text has been selected, the current source segment is written to
        this file. When the user exits OmegaT, this
        file is not emptied, in order to be consistent with usual clipboard
        behavior. The exported contents are copied to the file
        <filename>selection.txt</filename> located in the User's preference
        files folder.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>c</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry id="menus.edit.create.glossary.entry">
      <term id="menus.edit.create.glossary.entry.title">Create Glossary Entry</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Allows the user create an entry in the default glossary
        file.</para>
		
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>g</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

		<para>There are two ways to use this function. There first is to call
		the dialog and then to manually fill the various fields. The second is
		to select items in OmegaT's panes and to sequentially call the dialog
		after each selection to have OmegaT automatically enter the selection in
		the various fields:</para>

		<itemizedlist>
		  <listitem><para>Select a text string in any pane</para>
		  <para>Press
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>g</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		  </para>
		  <para>The selection will be entered in the <guilabel>Source
		  term</guilabel> field.</para></listitem>
		  <listitem><para>Select a text string in any pane</para>
		  <para>Press
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>g</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		  </para>
		  <para>The selection will be entered in the <guilabel>Target
		  term</guilabel> field.</para></listitem>
		  <listitem><para>[Optionnal] Select a text string in any pane</para>
		  <para>Press
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>g</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		  </para>
		  <para>The selection will be entered in the
		  <guilabel>Comment</guilabel> field.</para></listitem>
		  <listitem><para>Hit <guilabel>Enter</guilabel> or click on
		  <guilabel>OK</guilabel></para></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	  </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Search Project...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opens a new <link linkend="windows.text.search">Search
        window</link>.</para>

		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>f</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

        <para>If you select a text string (in any pane) before calling the
        function, the text will be pasted by default in the <guilabel>Search
        for</guilabel> field.</para>

		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>f</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		  displays the last already opened Search window (instead of opening a
		new one).</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Search and Replace...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opens a new <link linkend="windows.text.replace">Search
        and replace window</link>.</para>

		<para>
		  <keycombo>
            <keycap>C</keycap>
            <keycap>k</keycap>
          </keycombo>
		</para>
		
        <para>If you select a text string (in any pane) before calling the
        function, the text will be pasted by default in the <guilabel>Search
        for</guilabel> field.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Search Dictionaries</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>If <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.dictionary">automatic searching in dictionaries</link> is disabled, this function allows you to search for the selected word in the dictionaries.</para>

		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Switch case to</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Changes the case of the selected text in the target segment to
        the selected option, or cycle through the options. If no text is
        selected, OmegaT selects the word that contains the letter immediately
        to the right of the cursor.</para>
		<itemizedlist>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Lower Case</guilabel></para>
		  <para>all letters in lower case</para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Upper Case</guilabel></para>
		  <para>ALL LETTERS IN UPPER CASE</para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Title Case</guilabel></para>
		  <para>Almost all Letters in Lower Case</para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Sentence Case</guilabel></para>
		  <para>Only the first letter in upper case.</para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para>Cycle</para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>S</keycap>
              <keycap>F3</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
      <term>Select Match</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>Selects the previous, the next or the Nth fuzzy match displayed
		in the fuzzy match pane to replace or insert it to the segment.</para>
		<itemizedlist>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Previous Match</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>A</keycap>
              <keycap>↑</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Next Match</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>A</keycap>
              <keycap>↓</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Match #1</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>1</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Match #2</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>2</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Match #3</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>3</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Match #4</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>4</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Select Match #5</guilabel></para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>5</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>
		  </listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
      <term>Insert Unicode Control Character</term>
	  <listitem><para>Inserts the selected Unicode control character. See <link linkend="how.to.manage.right.to.left" endterm="how.to.manage.right.to.left.title"/> for details.</para>
		<itemizedlist>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Left-to-Right Mark (LRM U+200E)</guilabel></para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Right-to-Left Mark (RLM U+200F)</guilabel></para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Left-to-Right Embedding (LRE U+202A)</guilabel></para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para><guilabel>Right-to-Left Embedding (RLE U+202B)</guilabel></para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		  <listitem><para>Pop Directional Formatting (PDF U+202C)</para>
		  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		  </listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="menus.edit.use.as.default.translation">
      <term id="menus.edit.use.as.default.translation.title">Use as Default Translation</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>If there's several alternative translations available for the
		active segment, you can label the alternative selected as the default
		translation. The entry will be greyed, if there's just one translation
		available.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="menus.edit.create.alternative.translation">
      <term id="menus.edit.create.alternative.translation.title">Create Alternative Translation</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>The one and the same segment may, depending on the context,
		require different translations. Select this menu item, if the current
		translation does not apply and enter the alternative
		translation.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
      <term>Remove Translation</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>Deletes the translation and set the segment as
		untranslated.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
      <term>Set empty translation</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>Define the translation as being empty. In the target document,
		nothing will appear for this segment. In the Editor, the translation
		is displayed as &lt;EMPTY&gt;</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
      <term>Register Identical Translation</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>Use this command to register the translation to be identical to
		the source, even if <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.editor.allow.translation.to.be.equal.to.source"><guilabel>Allow
		translation to be equal to source</guilabel></link> is not
		checked.</para>
		  <para>
			<keycombo>
              <keycap>S</keycap>
              <keycap>C</keycap>
              <keycap>s</keycap>
			</keycombo>
		  </para>		
      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>
